<refentry xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" version="5.0-subset Scilab" xml:lang="en" xml:id="load_graph">
  <info>
    <pubdate>$LastChangedDate$</pubdate>
  </info>
  <refnamediv>
    <refname>load_graph</refname>
    <refpurpose> loads a graph from a file</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <title>Calling Sequence</title>
    <synopsis>[g,modified,mgs] = load_graph(name)</synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsection>
    <title>Parameters</title>
    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>name</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>string, the path of the file to load</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>g</term>
        <listitem>
          <para> a  <link linkend="graph_data_structure">graph_data_structure</link>.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>modified</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>a boolean, if true it indicates that the  graph list has been updated to the current version</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>msg</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>a string. if this argument is required the
          <literal>load_graph</literal> function returns on errors instead
          of calling the error manager. In such a case msg contains
          the error message. If no error occurs <literal>msg</literal> is an
          empty matrix.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsection>
  <refsection>
    <title>Description</title>
    <para><literal>load_graph</literal> loads a graph from a file. This file
    may be either an ascii file (scilab4.x versions) or a binary file
    compatible with the <literal>load</literal> and <literal>save</literal> functions.</para>
  </refsection>
  <refsection>
    <title>Examples</title>
    <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[

g=load_graph(metanet_module_path()+'/demos/mesh100.graph');
show_graph(g);
g=load_graph(metanet_module_path()+'/demos/colored.graph');
show_graph(g,'new');
 
  ]]></programlisting>
  </refsection>
